fields.description: The names and identifiers of organizational units that are in scope for a synchronization rule. containerFilter and groupFilter are mutually exclusive properties that cannot be configured in the same request. Currently only supported for Azure AD Connect cloud sync scenarios.
fields.name: ContainerFilter

fields.description: true if the synchronization rule can be customized; false if this rule is read-only and shouldn't be changed.
fields.name: Editable

fields.description: The names and identifiers of groups that are in scope for a synchronization rule. containerFilter and groupFilter are mutually exclusive properties that cannot be configured in the same request. Currently only supported for Azure AD Connect cloud sync scenarios.
fields.name: GroupFilter

fields.description: Synchronization rule identifier. Must be one of the identifiers recognized by the synchronization engine. Supported rule identifiers can be found in the synchronization template returned by the API.
fields.name: Id

fields.description: Additional extension properties. Unless instructed explicitly by the support team, metadata values shouldn't be changed.
fields.name: Metadata

fields.description: Human-readable name of the synchronization rule. Not nullable.
fields.name: Name

fields.description: The OData ID of this entity
fields.name: ODataId

fields.description: The OData Type of this entity
fields.name: ODataType

fields.description: Collection of object mappings supported by the rule. Tells the synchronization engine which objects should be synchronized.
fields.name: ObjectMappings

fields.description: Priority relative to other rules in the synchronizationSchema. Rules with the lowest priority number will be processed first.
fields.name: Priority

fields.description: Name of the source directory. Must match one of the directory definitions in synchronizationSchema.
fields.name: SourceDirectoryName

fields.description: Name of the target directory. Must match one of the directory definitions in synchronizationSchema.
fields.name: TargetDirectoryName
